7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This file contains a pass that performs load / store related peephole ----
10 // optimizations. This pass should be run after register allocation. ----
11 // ----
12 // The pass runs after the PrologEpilogInserter where we emit the CFI ----
13 // instructions. In order to preserve the correctness of the unwind informaiton, ----
14 // the pass should not change the order of any two instructions, one of which ----
15 // has the FrameSetup/FrameDestroy flag or, alternatively, apply an add-hoc fix ----
16 // to unwind information. ----
17 // ----
18 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
19 ----

87 using LdStPairFlags = struct LdStPairFlags { ----
88 // If a matching instruction is found, MergeForward is set to true if the ----
89 // merge is to remove the first instruction and replace the second with ----
90 // a pair-wise insn, and false if the reverse is true. ----
91 bool MergeForward = false; ----
92 ----
93 // SExtIdx gives the index of the result of the load pair that must be ----
94 // extended. The value of SExtIdx assumes that the paired load produces the ----
95 // value in this order: (I, returned iterator), i.e., -1 means no value has ----
96 // to be extended, 0 means I, and 1 means the returned iterator. ----
97 int SExtIdx = -1; ----
98 ----
99 // If not none, RenameReg can be used to rename the result register of the ----
100 // first store in a pair. Currently this only works when merging stores ----
101 // forward. ----
102 std::optional RenameReg; ----
103 ----
104 LdStPairFlags() = default; ----
105 ----
106 void setMergeForward(bool V = true) { MergeForward = V; } 0
107 bool getMergeForward() const { return MergeForward; } 0
108 ----
109 void setSExtIdx(int V) { SExtIdx = V; } 0
110 int getSExtIdx() const { return SExtIdx; } 0
111 ----
112 void setRenameReg(MCPhysReg R) { RenameReg = R; } 0
113 void clearRenameReg() { RenameReg = std::nullopt; } 0
114 std::optional getRenameReg() const { return RenameReg; } 0
115 }; ----

560 static bool isPreLdStPairCandidate(MachineInstr &FirstMI, MachineInstr &MI) { 0
561 ----
562 unsigned OpcA = FirstMI.getOpcode(); 0
563 unsigned OpcB = MI.getOpcode(); 0
564 ----
565 switch (OpcA) { 0
566 default: 0
567 return false; 0
568 case AArch64::STRSpre: 0
569 return (OpcB == AArch64::STRSui) || (OpcB == AArch64::STURSi); 0
570 case AArch64::STRDpre: 0
571 return (OpcB == AArch64::STRDui) || (OpcB == AArch64::STURDi); 0
572 case AArch64::STRQpre: 0
573 return (OpcB == AArch64::STRQui) || (OpcB == AArch64::STURQi); 0
574 case AArch64::STRWpre: 0
575 return (OpcB == AArch64::STRWui) || (OpcB == AArch64::STURWi); 0
576 case AArch64::STRXpre: 0
577 return (OpcB == AArch64::STRXui) || (OpcB == AArch64::STURXi); 0
578 case AArch64::LDRSpre: 0
579 return (OpcB == AArch64::LDRSui) || (OpcB == AArch64::LDURSi); 0
580 case AArch64::LDRDpre: 0
581 return (OpcB == AArch64::LDRDui) || (OpcB == AArch64::LDURDi); 0
582 case AArch64::LDRQpre: 0
583 return (OpcB == AArch64::LDRQui) || (OpcB == AArch64::LDURQi); 0
584 case AArch64::LDRWpre: 0
585 return (OpcB == AArch64::LDRWui) || (OpcB == AArch64::LDURWi); 0
586 case AArch64::LDRXpre: 0
587 return (OpcB == AArch64::LDRXui) || (OpcB == AArch64::LDURXi); 0
588 } ----

590 ----
591 // Returns the scale and offset range of pre/post indexed variants of MI. ----
592 static void getPrePostIndexedMemOpInfo(const MachineInstr &MI, int &Scale, 0
593 int &MinOffset, int &MaxOffset) { ----
594 bool IsPaired = AArch64InstrInfo::isPairedLdSt(MI); 0
595 bool IsTagStore = isTagStore(MI); 0
596 // ST*G and all paired ldst have the same scale in pre/post-indexed variants ----
597 // as in the "unsigned offset" variant. ----
598 // All other pre/post indexed ldst instructions are unscaled. ----
599 Scale = (IsTagStore || IsPaired) ? AArch64InstrInfo::getMemScale(MI) : 1; 0
600 ----
601 if (IsPaired) { 0
602 MinOffset = -64; 0
603 MaxOffset = 63; 0
604 } else { ----
605 MinOffset = -256; 0
606 MaxOffset = 255; 0
607 } ----
608 } 0
609 ----
610 static MachineOperand &getLdStRegOp(MachineInstr &MI, 0
611 unsigned PairedRegOp = 0) { ----
612 assert(PairedRegOp < 2 && "Unexpected register operand idx."); 0
613 bool IsPreLdSt = AArch64InstrInfo::isPreLdSt(MI); 0
614 if (IsPreLdSt) 0
615 PairedRegOp += 1; 0
616 unsigned Idx = ----
617 AArch64InstrInfo::isPairedLdSt(MI) || IsPreLdSt ? PairedRegOp : 0; 0
618 return MI.getOperand(Idx); 0
619 } ----
620 ----
621 static bool isLdOffsetInRangeOfSt(MachineInstr &LoadInst, 0
622 MachineInstr &StoreInst, ----
623 const AArch64InstrInfo *TII) { ----
624 assert(isMatchingStore(LoadInst, StoreInst) && "Expect only matched ld/st."); 0
625 int LoadSize = TII->getMemScale(LoadInst); 0
626 int StoreSize = TII->getMemScale(StoreInst); 0
627 int UnscaledStOffset = ----
628 TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(StoreInst) 0
629 ? AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(StoreInst).getImm() 0
630 : AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(StoreInst).getImm() * StoreSize; 0
631 int UnscaledLdOffset = ----
632 TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(LoadInst) 0
633 ? AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(LoadInst).getImm() 0
634 : AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(LoadInst).getImm() * LoadSize; 0
635 return (UnscaledStOffset <= UnscaledLdOffset) && 0
636 (UnscaledLdOffset + LoadSize <= (UnscaledStOffset + StoreSize)); 0
637 } ----
638 ----
639 static bool isPromotableZeroStoreInst(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
640 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
641 return (Opc == AArch64::STRWui || Opc == AArch64::STURWi || 0
642 isNarrowStore(Opc)) && 0
643 getLdStRegOp(MI).getReg() == AArch64::WZR; 0
644 } ----
645 ----
646 static bool isPromotableLoadFromStore(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
647 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
648 default: 0
649 return false; 0
650 // Scaled instructions. ----
651 case AArch64::LDRBBui: 0
652 case AArch64::LDRHHui: ----
653 case AArch64::LDRWui: ----
654 case AArch64::LDRXui: ----
655 // Unscaled instructions. ----
656 case AArch64::LDURBBi: ----
657 case AArch64::LDURHHi: ----
658 case AArch64::LDURWi: ----
659 case AArch64::LDURXi: ----
660 return true; 0
661 } ----
662 } ----
663 ----
664 static bool isMergeableLdStUpdate(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
665 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
666 switch (Opc) { 0
667 default: 0
668 return false; 0
669 // Scaled instructions. ----
670 case AArch64::STRSui: 0
671 case AArch64::STRDui: ----
672 case AArch64::STRQui: ----
673 case AArch64::STRXui: ----
674 case AArch64::STRWui: ----
675 case AArch64::STRHHui: ----
676 case AArch64::STRBBui: ----
677 case AArch64::LDRSui: ----
678 case AArch64::LDRDui: ----
679 case AArch64::LDRQui: ----
680 case AArch64::LDRXui: ----
681 case AArch64::LDRWui: ----
682 case AArch64::LDRHHui: ----
683 case AArch64::LDRBBui: ----
684 case AArch64::STGi: ----
685 case AArch64::STZGi: ----
686 case AArch64::ST2Gi: ----
687 case AArch64::STZ2Gi: ----
688 case AArch64::STGPi: ----
689 // Unscaled instructions. ----
690 case AArch64::STURSi: ----
691 case AArch64::STURDi: ----
692 case AArch64::STURQi: ----
693 case AArch64::STURWi: ----
694 case AArch64::STURXi: ----
695 case AArch64::LDURSi: ----
696 case AArch64::LDURDi: ----
697 case AArch64::LDURQi: ----
698 case AArch64::LDURWi: ----
699 case AArch64::LDURXi: ----
700 // Paired instructions. ----
701 case AArch64::LDPSi: ----
702 case AArch64::LDPSWi: ----
703 case AArch64::LDPDi: ----
704 case AArch64::LDPQi: ----
705 case AArch64::LDPWi: ----
706 case AArch64::LDPXi: ----
707 case AArch64::STPSi: ----
708 case AArch64::STPDi: ----
709 case AArch64::STPQi: ----
710 case AArch64::STPWi: ----
711 case AArch64::STPXi: ----
712 // Make sure this is a reg+imm (as opposed to an address reloc). ----
713 if (!AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MI).isImm()) 0
714 return false; 0
715 ----
716 return true; 0
717 } ----
718 } ----
719 ----
720 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
721 AArch64LoadStoreOpt::mergeNarrowZeroStores(MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, 0
722 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MergeMI, ----
723 const LdStPairFlags &Flags) { ----
724 assert(isPromotableZeroStoreInst(*I) && isPromotableZeroStoreInst(*MergeMI) && 0
725 "Expected promotable zero stores."); ----
726 ----
727 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = I->getParent()->end(); 0
728 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NextI = next_nodbg(I, E); 0
729 // If NextI is the second of the two instructions to be merged, we need ----
730 // to skip one further. Either way we merge will invalidate the iterator, ----
731 // and we don't need to scan the new instruction, as it's a pairwise ----
732 // instruction, which we're not considering for further action anyway. ----
733 if (NextI == MergeMI) 0
734 NextI = next_nodbg(NextI, E); 0
735 ----
736 unsigned Opc = I->getOpcode(); 0
737 unsigned MergeMIOpc = MergeMI->getOpcode(); 0
738 bool IsScaled = !TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(Opc); 0
739 bool IsMergedMIScaled = !TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(MergeMIOpc); 0
740 int OffsetStride = IsScaled ? TII->getMemScale(*I) : 1; 0
741 int MergeMIOffsetStride = IsMergedMIScaled ? TII->getMemScale(*MergeMI) : 1; 0
742 ----
743 bool MergeForward = Flags.getMergeForward(); 0
744 // Insert our new paired instruction after whichever of the paired ----
745 // instructions MergeForward indicates. ----
746 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertionPoint = MergeForward ? MergeMI : I; 0
747 // Also based on MergeForward is from where we copy the base register operand ----
748 // so we get the flags compatible with the input code. ----
749 const MachineOperand &BaseRegOp = ----
750 MergeForward ? AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(*MergeMI) 0
751 : AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(*I); 0
752 ----
753 // Which register is Rt and which is Rt2 depends on the offset order. ----
754 int64_t IOffsetInBytes = ----
755 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*I).getImm() * OffsetStride; 0
756 int64_t MIOffsetInBytes = ----
757 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*MergeMI).getImm() * 0
758 MergeMIOffsetStride; 0
759 // Select final offset based on the offset order. ----
760 int64_t OffsetImm; ----
761 if (IOffsetInBytes > MIOffsetInBytes) 0
762 OffsetImm = MIOffsetInBytes; 0
763 else ----
764 OffsetImm = IOffsetInBytes; 0
765 ----
766 int NewOpcode = getMatchingWideOpcode(Opc); 0
767 bool FinalIsScaled = !TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(NewOpcode); 0
768 ----
769 // Adjust final offset if the result opcode is a scaled store. ----
770 if (FinalIsScaled) { 0
771 int NewOffsetStride = FinalIsScaled ? TII->getMemScale(NewOpcode) : 1; 0
772 assert(((OffsetImm % NewOffsetStride) == 0) && 0
773 "Offset should be a multiple of the store memory scale"); ----
774 OffsetImm = OffsetImm / NewOffsetStride; 0
775 } ----
776 ----
777 // Construct the new instruction. ----
778 DebugLoc DL = I->getDebugLoc(); 0
779 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = I->getParent(); 0
780 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
781 MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertionPoint, DL, TII->get(getMatchingWideOpcode(Opc))) 0
782 .addReg(isNarrowStore(Opc) ? AArch64::WZR : AArch64::XZR) 0
783 .add(BaseRegOp) 0
784 .addImm(OffsetImm) 0
785 .cloneMergedMemRefs({&*I, &*MergeMI}) 0
786 .setMIFlags(I->mergeFlagsWith(*MergeMI)); 0
787 (void)MIB; ----
788 ----
789 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Creating wider store. Replacing instructions:\n "); 0
790 LLVM_DEBUG(I->print(dbgs())); 0
791 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "); 0
792 LLVM_DEBUG(MergeMI->print(dbgs())); 0
793 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " with instruction:\n "); 0
794 LLVM_DEBUG(((MachineInstr *)MIB)->print(dbgs())); 0
795 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
796 ----
797 // Erase the old instructions. ----
798 I->eraseFromParent(); 0
799 MergeMI->eraseFromParent(); 0
800 return NextI; 0
801 } 0
802 ----
803 // Apply Fn to all instructions between MI and the beginning of the block, until ----
804 // a def for DefReg is reached. Returns true, iff Fn returns true for all ----
805 // visited instructions. Stop after visiting Limit iterations. ----
806 static bool forAllMIsUntilDef(MachineInstr &MI, MCPhysReg DefReg, 0
807 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, unsigned Limit, ----
808 std::function &Fn) { ----
809 auto MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
810 for (MachineInstr &I : 0
811 instructionsWithoutDebug(MI.getReverseIterator(), MBB->instr_rend())) { 0
812 if (!Limit) 0
813 return false; 0
814 --Limit; 0
815 ----
816 bool isDef = any_of(I.operands(), [DefReg, TRI](MachineOperand &MOP) { 0
817 return MOP.isReg() && MOP.isDef() && !MOP.isDebug() && MOP.getReg() && 0
818 TRI->regsOverlap(MOP.getReg(), DefReg); 0
819 }); ----
820 if (!Fn(I, isDef)) 0
821 return false; 0
822 if (isDef) 0
823 break; 0
824 } ----
825 return true; 0
826 } ----
827 ----
828 static void updateDefinedRegisters(MachineInstr &MI, LiveRegUnits &Units, 0
829 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
830 ----
831 for (const MachineOperand &MOP : phys_regs_and_masks(MI)) 0
832 if (MOP.isReg() && MOP.isKill()) 0
833 Units.removeReg(MOP.getReg()); 0
834 ----
835 for (const MachineOperand &MOP : phys_regs_and_masks(MI)) 0
836 if (MOP.isReg() && !MOP.isKill()) 0
837 Units.addReg(MOP.getReg()); 0
838 } 0
839 ----
840 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
841 AArch64LoadStoreOpt::mergePairedInsns(MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, 0
842 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Paired, ----
843 const LdStPairFlags &Flags) { ----
844 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = I->getParent()->end(); 0
845 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NextI = next_nodbg(I, E); 0
846 // If NextI is the second of the two instructions to be merged, we need ----
847 // to skip one further. Either way we merge will invalidate the iterator, ----
848 // and we don't need to scan the new instruction, as it's a pairwise ----
849 // instruction, which we're not considering for further action anyway. ----
850 if (NextI == Paired) 0
851 NextI = next_nodbg(NextI, E); 0
852 ----
853 int SExtIdx = Flags.getSExtIdx(); 0
854 unsigned Opc = ----
855 SExtIdx == -1 ? I->getOpcode() : getMatchingNonSExtOpcode(I->getOpcode()); 0
856 bool IsUnscaled = TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(Opc); 0
857 int OffsetStride = IsUnscaled ? TII->getMemScale(*I) : 1; 0
858 ----
859 bool MergeForward = Flags.getMergeForward(); 0
860 ----
861 std::optional RenameReg = Flags.getRenameReg(); 0
862 if (MergeForward && RenameReg) { 0
863 MCRegister RegToRename = getLdStRegOp(*I).getReg(); 0
864 DefinedInBB.addReg(*RenameReg); 0
865 ----
866 // Return the sub/super register for RenameReg, matching the size of ----
867 // OriginalReg. ----
868 auto GetMatchingSubReg = [this, 0
869 RenameReg](MCPhysReg OriginalReg) -> MCPhysReg { 0
870 for (MCPhysReg SubOrSuper : TRI->sub_and_superregs_inclusive(*RenameReg)) 0
871 if (TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(OriginalReg) == 0
872 TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(SubOrSuper)) 0
873 return SubOrSuper; 0
874 llvm_unreachable("Should have found matching sub or super register!"); 0
875 }; 0
876 ----
877 std::function UpdateMIs = ----
878 [this, RegToRename, GetMatchingSubReg](MachineInstr &MI, bool IsDef) { 0
879 if (IsDef) { 0
880 bool SeenDef = false; 0
881 for (auto &MOP : MI.operands()) { 0
882 // Rename the first explicit definition and all implicit ----
883 // definitions matching RegToRename. ----
884 if (MOP.isReg() && !MOP.isDebug() && MOP.getReg() && 0
885 (!SeenDef || (MOP.isDef() && MOP.isImplicit())) && 0
886 TRI->regsOverlap(MOP.getReg(), RegToRename)) { 0
887 assert((MOP.isImplicit() || 0
888 (MOP.isRenamable() && !MOP.isEarlyClobber())) && ----
889 "Need renamable operands"); ----
890 MOP.setReg(GetMatchingSubReg(MOP.getReg())); 0
891 SeenDef = true; 0
892 } ----
893 } ----
894 } else { ----
895 for (auto &MOP : MI.operands()) { 0
896 if (MOP.isReg() && !MOP.isDebug() && MOP.getReg() && 0
897 TRI->regsOverlap(MOP.getReg(), RegToRename)) { 0
898 assert((MOP.isImplicit() || 0
899 (MOP.isRenamable() && !MOP.isEarlyClobber())) && ----
900 "Need renamable operands"); ----
901 MOP.setReg(GetMatchingSubReg(MOP.getReg())); 0
902 } ----
903 } ----
904 } ----
905 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Renamed " << MI << "\n"); 0
906 return true; 0
907 }; 0
908 forAllMIsUntilDef(*I, RegToRename, TRI, LdStLimit, UpdateMIs); 0
909 ----
910 #if !defined(NDEBUG) ----
911 // Make sure the register used for renaming is not used between the paired ----
912 // instructions. That would trash the content before the new paired ----
913 // instruction. ----
914 for (auto &MI : 0
915 iterator_range>( ----
916 std::next(I), std::next(Paired))) 0
917 assert(all_of(MI.operands(), 0
918 [this, &RenameReg](const MachineOperand &MOP) { ----
919 return !MOP.isReg() || MOP.isDebug() || !MOP.getReg() || ----
920 MOP.isUndef() || ----
921 !TRI->regsOverlap(MOP.getReg(), *RenameReg); ----
922 }) && ----
923 "Rename register used between paired instruction, trashing the " ----
924 "content"); ----
925 #endif ----
926 } 0
927 ----
928 // Insert our new paired instruction after whichever of the paired ----
929 // instructions MergeForward indicates. ----
930 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertionPoint = MergeForward ? Paired : I; 0
931 // Also based on MergeForward is from where we copy the base register operand ----
932 // so we get the flags compatible with the input code. ----
933 const MachineOperand &BaseRegOp = ----
934 MergeForward ? AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(*Paired) 0
935 : AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(*I); 0
936 ----
937 int Offset = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*I).getImm(); 0
938 int PairedOffset = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*Paired).getImm(); 0
939 bool PairedIsUnscaled = TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(Paired->getOpcode()); 0
940 if (IsUnscaled != PairedIsUnscaled) { 0
941 // We're trying to pair instructions that differ in how they are scaled. If ----
942 // I is scaled then scale the offset of Paired accordingly. Otherwise, do ----
943 // the opposite (i.e., make Paired's offset unscaled). ----
944 int MemSize = TII->getMemScale(*Paired); 0
945 if (PairedIsUnscaled) { 0
946 // If the unscaled offset isn't a multiple of the MemSize, we can't ----
947 // pair the operations together. ----
948 assert(!(PairedOffset % TII->getMemScale(*Paired)) && 0
949 "Offset should be a multiple of the stride!"); ----
950 PairedOffset /= MemSize; 0
951 } else { ----
952 PairedOffset *= MemSize; 0
953 } ----
954 } ----
955 ----
956 // Which register is Rt and which is Rt2 depends on the offset order. ----
957 // However, for pre load/stores the Rt should be the one of the pre ----
958 // load/store. ----
959 MachineInstr *RtMI, *Rt2MI; ----
960 if (Offset == PairedOffset + OffsetStride && 0
961 !AArch64InstrInfo::isPreLdSt(*I)) { 0
962 RtMI = &*Paired; 0
963 Rt2MI = &*I; 0
964 // Here we swapped the assumption made for SExtIdx. ----
965 // I.e., we turn ldp I, Paired into ldp Paired, I. ----
966 // Update the index accordingly. ----
967 if (SExtIdx != -1) 0
968 SExtIdx = (SExtIdx + 1) % 2; 0
969 } else { ----
970 RtMI = &*I; 0
971 Rt2MI = &*Paired; 0
972 } ----
973 int OffsetImm = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*RtMI).getImm(); 0
974 // Scale the immediate offset, if necessary. ----
975 if (TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(RtMI->getOpcode())) { 0
976 assert(!(OffsetImm % TII->getMemScale(*RtMI)) && 0
977 "Unscaled offset cannot be scaled."); ----
978 OffsetImm /= TII->getMemScale(*RtMI); 0
979 } ----
980 ----
981 // Construct the new instruction. ----
982 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
983 DebugLoc DL = I->getDebugLoc(); 0
984 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = I->getParent(); 0
985 MachineOperand RegOp0 = getLdStRegOp(*RtMI); 0
986 MachineOperand RegOp1 = getLdStRegOp(*Rt2MI); 0
987 // Kill flags may become invalid when moving stores for pairing. ----
988 if (RegOp0.isUse()) { 0
989 if (!MergeForward) { 0
990 // Clear kill flags on store if moving upwards. Example: ----
991 // STRWui %w0, ... ----
992 // USE %w1 ----
993 // STRWui kill %w1 ; need to clear kill flag when moving STRWui upwards ----
994 RegOp0.setIsKill(false); 0
995 RegOp1.setIsKill(false); 0
996 } else { ----
997 // Clear kill flags of the first stores register. Example: ----
998 // STRWui %w1, ... ----
999 // USE kill %w1 ; need to clear kill flag when moving STRWui downwards ----
1000 // STRW %w0 ----
1001 Register Reg = getLdStRegOp(*I).getReg(); 0
1002 for (MachineInstr &MI : make_range(std::next(I), Paired)) 0
1003 MI.clearRegisterKills(Reg, TRI); 0
1004 } ----
1005 } ----
1006 ----
1007 unsigned int MatchPairOpcode = getMatchingPairOpcode(Opc); 0
1008 MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertionPoint, DL, TII->get(MatchPairOpcode)); 0
1009 ----
1010 // Adds the pre-index operand for pre-indexed ld/st pairs. ----
1011 if (AArch64InstrInfo::isPreLdSt(*RtMI)) 0
1012 MIB.addReg(BaseRegOp.getReg(), RegState::Define); 0
1013 ----
1014 MIB.add(RegOp0) 0
1015 .add(RegOp1) 0
1016 .add(BaseRegOp) 0
1017 .addImm(OffsetImm) 0
1018 .cloneMergedMemRefs({&*I, &*Paired}) 0
1019 .setMIFlags(I->mergeFlagsWith(*Paired)); 0
1020 ----
1021 (void)MIB; ----
1022 ----
1023 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1024 dbgs() << "Creating pair load/store. Replacing instructions:\n "); ----
1025 LLVM_DEBUG(I->print(dbgs())); 0
1026 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "); 0
1027 LLVM_DEBUG(Paired->print(dbgs())); 0
1028 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " with instruction:\n "); 0
1029 if (SExtIdx != -1) { 0
1030 // Generate the sign extension for the proper result of the ldp. ----
1031 // I.e., with X1, that would be: ----
1032 // %w1 = KILL %w1, implicit-def %x1 ----
1033 // %x1 = SBFMXri killed %x1, 0, 31 ----
1034 MachineOperand &DstMO = MIB->getOperand(SExtIdx); 0
1035 // Right now, DstMO has the extended register, since it comes from an ----
1036 // extended opcode. ----
1037 Register DstRegX = DstMO.getReg(); 0
1038 // Get the W variant of that register. ----
1039 Register DstRegW = TRI->getSubReg(DstRegX, AArch64::sub_32); 0
1040 // Update the result of LDP to use the W instead of the X variant. ----
1041 DstMO.setReg(DstRegW); 0
1042 LLVM_DEBUG(((MachineInstr *)MIB)->print(dbgs())); 0
1043 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1044 // Make the machine verifier happy by providing a definition for ----
1045 // the X register. ----
1046 // Insert this definition right after the generated LDP, i.e., before ----
1047 // InsertionPoint. ----
1048 MachineInstrBuilder MIBKill = ----
1049 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertionPoint, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::KILL), DstRegW) 0
1050 .addReg(DstRegW) 0
1051 .addReg(DstRegX, RegState::Define); 0
1052 MIBKill->getOperand(2).setImplicit(); 0
1053 // Create the sign extension. ----
1054 MachineInstrBuilder MIBSXTW = ----
1055 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertionPoint, DL, TII->get(AArch64::SBFMXri), DstRegX) 0
1056 .addReg(DstRegX) 0
1057 .addImm(0) 0
1058 .addImm(31); 0
1059 (void)MIBSXTW; ----
1060 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Extend operand:\n "); 0
1061 LLVM_DEBUG(((MachineInstr *)MIBSXTW)->print(dbgs())); 0
1062 } else { ----
1063 LLVM_DEBUG(((MachineInstr *)MIB)->print(dbgs())); 0
1064 } ----
1065 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1066 ----
1067 if (MergeForward) 0
1068 for (const MachineOperand &MOP : phys_regs_and_masks(*I)) 0
1069 if (MOP.isReg() && MOP.isKill()) 0
1070 DefinedInBB.addReg(MOP.getReg()); 0
1071 ----
1072 // Erase the old instructions. ----
1073 I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1074 Paired->eraseFromParent(); 0
1075 ----
1076 return NextI; 0
1077 } 0
1078 ----
1079 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1080 AArch64LoadStoreOpt::promoteLoadFromStore(MachineBasicBlock::iterator LoadI, 0
1081 MachineBasicBlock::iterator StoreI) { ----
1082 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NextI = ----
1083 next_nodbg(LoadI, LoadI->getParent()->end()); 0
1084 ----
1085 int LoadSize = TII->getMemScale(*LoadI); 0
1086 int StoreSize = TII->getMemScale(*StoreI); 0
1087 Register LdRt = getLdStRegOp(*LoadI).getReg(); 0
1088 const MachineOperand &StMO = getLdStRegOp(*StoreI); 0
1089 Register StRt = getLdStRegOp(*StoreI).getReg(); 0
1090 bool IsStoreXReg = TRI->getRegClass(AArch64::GPR64RegClassID)->contains(StRt); 0
1091 ----
1092 assert((IsStoreXReg || 0
1093 TRI->getRegClass(AArch64::GPR32RegClassID)->contains(StRt)) && ----
1094 "Unexpected RegClass"); ----
1095 ----
1096 MachineInstr *BitExtMI; ----
1097 if (LoadSize == StoreSize && (LoadSize == 4 || LoadSize == 8)) { 0
1098 // Remove the load, if the destination register of the loads is the same ----
1099 // register for stored value. ----
1100 if (StRt == LdRt && LoadSize == 8) { 0
1101 for (MachineInstr &MI : make_range(StoreI->getIterator(), 0
1102 LoadI->getIterator())) { 0
1103 if (MI.killsRegister(StRt, TRI)) { 0
1104 MI.clearRegisterKills(StRt, TRI); 0
1105 break; 0
1106 } ----
1107 } ----
1108 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Remove load instruction:\n "); 0
1109 LLVM_DEBUG(LoadI->print(dbgs())); 0
1110 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1111 LoadI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1112 return NextI; 0
1113 } ----
1114 // Replace the load with a mov if the load and store are in the same size. ----
1115 BitExtMI = ----
1116 BuildMI(*LoadI->getParent(), LoadI, LoadI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1117 TII->get(IsStoreXReg ? AArch64::ORRXrs : AArch64::ORRWrs), LdRt) 0
1118 .addReg(IsStoreXReg ? AArch64::XZR : AArch64::WZR) 0
1119 .add(StMO) 0
1120 .addImm(AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSL, 0)) 0
1121 .setMIFlags(LoadI->getFlags()); 0
1122 } else { 0
1123 // FIXME: Currently we disable this transformation in big-endian targets as ----
1124 // performance and correctness are verified only in little-endian. ----
1125 if (!Subtarget->isLittleEndian()) 0
1126 return NextI; 0
1127 bool IsUnscaled = TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(*LoadI); 0
1128 assert(IsUnscaled == TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(*StoreI) && 0
1129 "Unsupported ld/st match"); ----
1130 assert(LoadSize <= StoreSize && "Invalid load size"); 0
1131 int UnscaledLdOffset = ----
1132 IsUnscaled ----
1133 ? AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*LoadI).getImm() 0
1134 : AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*LoadI).getImm() * LoadSize; 0
1135 int UnscaledStOffset = ----
1136 IsUnscaled ----
1137 ? AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*StoreI).getImm() 0
1138 : AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(*StoreI).getImm() * StoreSize; 0
1139 int Width = LoadSize * 8; 0
1140 Register DestReg = ----
1141 IsStoreXReg ? Register(TRI->getMatchingSuperReg( 0
1142 LdRt, AArch64::sub_32, &AArch64::GPR64RegClass)) ----
1143 : LdRt; 0
1144 ----
1145 assert((UnscaledLdOffset >= UnscaledStOffset && 0
1146 (UnscaledLdOffset + LoadSize) <= UnscaledStOffset + StoreSize) && ----
1147 "Invalid offset"); ----
1148 ----
1149 int Immr = 8 * (UnscaledLdOffset - UnscaledStOffset); 0
1150 int Imms = Immr + Width - 1; 0
1151 if (UnscaledLdOffset == UnscaledStOffset) { 0
1152 uint32_t AndMaskEncoded = ((IsStoreXReg ? 1 : 0) << 12) // N 0
1153 | ((Immr) << 6) // immr 0
1154 | ((Imms) << 0) // imms 0
1155 ; ----
1156 ----
1157 BitExtMI = ----
1158 BuildMI(*LoadI->getParent(), LoadI, LoadI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1159 TII->get(IsStoreXReg ? AArch64::ANDXri : AArch64::ANDWri), 0
1160 DestReg) ----
1161 .add(StMO) 0
1162 .addImm(AndMaskEncoded) 0
1163 .setMIFlags(LoadI->getFlags()); 0
1164 } else { ----
1165 BitExtMI = ----
1166 BuildMI(*LoadI->getParent(), LoadI, LoadI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1167 TII->get(IsStoreXReg ? AArch64::UBFMXri : AArch64::UBFMWri), 0
1168 DestReg) ----
1169 .add(StMO) 0
1170 .addImm(Immr) 0
1171 .addImm(Imms) 0
1172 .setMIFlags(LoadI->getFlags()); 0
1173 } ----
1174 } ----
1175 ----
1176 // Clear kill flags between store and load. ----
1177 for (MachineInstr &MI : make_range(StoreI->getIterator(), 0
1178 BitExtMI->getIterator())) 0
1179 if (MI.killsRegister(StRt, TRI)) { 0
1180 MI.clearRegisterKills(StRt, TRI); 0
1181 break; 0
1182 } ----
1183 ----
1184 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Promoting load by replacing :\n "); 0
1185 LLVM_DEBUG(StoreI->print(dbgs())); 0
1186 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "); 0
1187 LLVM_DEBUG(LoadI->print(dbgs())); 0
1188 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " with instructions:\n "); 0
1189 LLVM_DEBUG(StoreI->print(dbgs())); 0
1190 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "); 0
1191 LLVM_DEBUG((BitExtMI)->print(dbgs())); 0
1192 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1193 ----
1194 // Erase the old instructions. ----
1195 LoadI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1196 return NextI; 0
1197 } ----
1198 ----
1199 static bool inBoundsForPair(bool IsUnscaled, int Offset, int OffsetStride) { 0
1200 // Convert the byte-offset used by unscaled into an "element" offset used ----
1201 // by the scaled pair load/store instructions. ----
1202 if (IsUnscaled) { 0
1203 // If the byte-offset isn't a multiple of the stride, there's no point ----
1204 // trying to match it. ----
1205 if (Offset % OffsetStride) 0
1206 return false; 0
1207 Offset /= OffsetStride; 0
1208 } ----
1209 return Offset <= 63 && Offset >= -64; 0
1210 } ----
1211 ----
1212 // Do alignment, specialized to power of 2 and for signed ints, ----
1213 // avoiding having to do a C-style cast from uint_64t to int when ----
1214 // using alignTo from include/llvm/Support/MathExtras.h. ----
1215 // FIXME: Move this function to include/MathExtras.h? ----
1216 static int alignTo(int Num, int PowOf2) { 0
1217 return (Num + PowOf2 - 1) & ~(PowOf2 - 1); 0
1218 } ----
1219 ----
1220 static bool mayAlias(MachineInstr &MIa, 0
1221 SmallVectorImpl &MemInsns, ----
1222 AliasAnalysis *AA) { ----
1223 for (MachineInstr *MIb : MemInsns) 0
1224 if (MIa.mayAlias(AA, *MIb, /*UseTBAA*/ false)) 0
1225 return true; 0
1226 ----
1227 return false; 0
1228 } ----
1229 ----
1230 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::findMatchingStore( 0
1231 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, unsigned Limit, ----
1232 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &StoreI) { ----
1233 MachineBasicBlock::iterator B = I->getParent()->begin(); 0
1234 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = I; 0
1235 MachineInstr &LoadMI = *I; 0
1236 Register BaseReg = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(LoadMI).getReg(); 0
1237 ----
1238 // If the load is the first instruction in the block, there's obviously ----
1239 // not any matching store. ----
1240 if (MBBI == B) 0
1241 return false; 0
1242 ----
1243 // Track which register units have been modified and used between the first ----
1244 // insn and the second insn. ----
1245 ModifiedRegUnits.clear(); 0
1246 UsedRegUnits.clear(); 0
1247 ----
1248 unsigned Count = 0; 0
1249 do { ----
1250 MBBI = prev_nodbg(MBBI, B); 0
1251 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1252 ----
1253 // Don't count transient instructions towards the search limit since there ----
1254 // may be different numbers of them if e.g. debug information is present. ----
1255 if (!MI.isTransient()) 0
1256 ++Count; 0
1257 ----
1258 // If the load instruction reads directly from the address to which the ----
1259 // store instruction writes and the stored value is not modified, we can ----
1260 // promote the load. Since we do not handle stores with pre-/post-index, ----
1261 // it's unnecessary to check if BaseReg is modified by the store itself. ----
1262 // Also we can't handle stores without an immediate offset operand, ----
1263 // while the operand might be the address for a global variable. ----
1264 if (MI.mayStore() && isMatchingStore(LoadMI, MI) && 0
1265 BaseReg == AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MI).getReg() && 0
1266 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MI).isImm() && 0
1267 isLdOffsetInRangeOfSt(LoadMI, MI, TII) && 0
1268 ModifiedRegUnits.available(getLdStRegOp(MI).getReg())) { 0
1269 StoreI = MBBI; 0
1270 return true; 0
1271 } ----
1272 ----
1273 if (MI.isCall()) 0
1274 return false; 0
1275 ----
1276 // Update modified / uses register units. ----
1277 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1278 ----
1279 // Otherwise, if the base register is modified, we have no match, so ----
1280 // return early. ----
1281 if (!ModifiedRegUnits.available(BaseReg)) 0
1282 return false; 0
1283 ----
1284 // If we encounter a store aliased with the load, return early. ----
1285 if (MI.mayStore() && LoadMI.mayAlias(AA, MI, /*UseTBAA*/ false)) 0
1286 return false; 0
1287 } while (MBBI != B && Count < Limit); 0
1288 return false; 0
1289 } ----
1290 ----
1291 static bool needsWinCFI(const MachineFunction *MF) { 0
1292 return MF->getTarget().getMCAsmInfo()->usesWindowsCFI() && 0
1293 MF->getFunction().needsUnwindTableEntry(); 0
1294 } ----
1295 ----
1296 // Returns true if FirstMI and MI are candidates for merging or pairing. ----
1297 // Otherwise, returns false. ----
1298 static bool areCandidatesToMergeOrPair(MachineInstr &FirstMI, MachineInstr &MI, 0
1299 LdStPairFlags &Flags, ----
1300 const AArch64InstrInfo *TII) { ----
1301 // If this is volatile or if pairing is suppressed, not a candidate. ----
1302 if (MI.hasOrderedMemoryRef() || TII->isLdStPairSuppressed(MI)) 0
1303 return false; 0
1304 ----
1305 // We should have already checked FirstMI for pair suppression and volatility. ----
1306 assert(!FirstMI.hasOrderedMemoryRef() && 0
1307 !TII->isLdStPairSuppressed(FirstMI) && ----
1308 "FirstMI shouldn't get here if either of these checks are true."); ----
1309 ----
1310 if (needsWinCFI(MI.getMF()) && (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup) || 0
1311 MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameDestroy))) 0
1312 return false; 0
1313 ----
1314 unsigned OpcA = FirstMI.getOpcode(); 0
1315 unsigned OpcB = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1316 ----
1317 // Opcodes match: If the opcodes are pre ld/st there is nothing more to check. ----
1318 if (OpcA == OpcB) 0
1319 return !AArch64InstrInfo::isPreLdSt(FirstMI); 0
1320 ----
1321 // Try to match a sign-extended load/store with a zero-extended load/store. ----
1322 bool IsValidLdStrOpc, PairIsValidLdStrOpc; ----
1323 unsigned NonSExtOpc = getMatchingNonSExtOpcode(OpcA, &IsValidLdStrOpc); 0
1324 assert(IsValidLdStrOpc && 0
1325 "Given Opc should be a Load or Store with an immediate"); ----
1326 // OpcA will be the first instruction in the pair. ----
1327 if (NonSExtOpc == getMatchingNonSExtOpcode(OpcB, &PairIsValidLdStrOpc)) { 0
1328 Flags.setSExtIdx(NonSExtOpc == (unsigned)OpcA ? 1 : 0); 0
1329 return true; 0
1330 } ----
1331 ----
1332 // If the second instruction isn't even a mergable/pairable load/store, bail ----
1333 // out. ----
1334 if (!PairIsValidLdStrOpc) 0
1335 return false; 0
1336 ----
1337 // FIXME: We don't support merging narrow stores with mixed scaled/unscaled ----
1338 // offsets. ----
1339 if (isNarrowStore(OpcA) || isNarrowStore(OpcB)) 0
1340 return false; 0
1341 ----
1342 // The STRpre - STRui and ----
1343 // LDRpre-LDRui ----
1344 // are candidate pairs that can be merged. ----
1345 if (isPreLdStPairCandidate(FirstMI, MI)) 0
1346 return true; 0
1347 ----
1348 // Try to match an unscaled load/store with a scaled load/store. ----
1349 return TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(OpcA) != TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(OpcB) && 0
1350 getMatchingPairOpcode(OpcA) == getMatchingPairOpcode(OpcB); 0
1351 ----
1352 // FIXME: Can we also match a mixed sext/zext unscaled/scaled pair? ----
1353 } ----
1354 ----
1355 static bool ----
1356 canRenameUpToDef(MachineInstr &FirstMI, LiveRegUnits &UsedInBetween, 0
1357 SmallPtrSetImpl &RequiredClasses, ----
1358 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1359 if (!FirstMI.mayStore()) 0
1360 return false; 0
1361 ----
1362 // Check if we can find an unused register which we can use to rename ----
1363 // the register used by the first load/store. ----
1364 auto *RegClass = TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(getLdStRegOp(FirstMI).getReg()); 0
1365 MachineFunction &MF = *FirstMI.getParent()->getParent(); 0
1366 if (!RegClass || !MF.getRegInfo().tracksLiveness()) 0
1367 return false; 0
1368 ----
1369 auto RegToRename = getLdStRegOp(FirstMI).getReg(); 0
1370 // For now, we only rename if the store operand gets killed at the store. ----
1371 if (!getLdStRegOp(FirstMI).isKill() && 0
1372 !any_of(FirstMI.operands(), 0
1373 [TRI, RegToRename](const MachineOperand &MOP) { 0
1374 return MOP.isReg() && !MOP.isDebug() && MOP.getReg() && 0
1375 MOP.isImplicit() && MOP.isKill() && 0
1376 TRI->regsOverlap(RegToRename, MOP.getReg()); 0
1377 })) { ----
1378 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Operand not killed at " << FirstMI << "\n"); 0
1379 return false; 0
1380 } ----
1381 auto canRenameMOP = [TRI](const MachineOperand &MOP) { 0
1382 if (MOP.isReg()) { 0
1383 auto *RegClass = TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(MOP.getReg()); 0
1384 // Renaming registers with multiple disjunct sub-registers (e.g. the ----
1385 // result of a LD3) means that all sub-registers are renamed, potentially ----
1386 // impacting other instructions we did not check. Bail out. ----
1387 // Note that this relies on the structure of the AArch64 register file. In ----
1388 // particular, a subregister cannot be written without overwriting the ----
1389 // whole register. ----
1390 if (RegClass->HasDisjunctSubRegs) { 0
1391 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1392 dbgs() ----
1393 << " Cannot rename operands with multiple disjunct subregisters (" ----
1394 << MOP << ")\n"); ----
1395 return false; 0
1396 } ----
1397 } ----
1398 return MOP.isImplicit() || 0
1399 (MOP.isRenamable() && !MOP.isEarlyClobber() && !MOP.isTied()); 0
1400 }; 0
1401 ----
1402 bool FoundDef = false; 0
1403 ----
1404 // For each instruction between FirstMI and the previous def for RegToRename, ----
1405 // we ----
1406 // * check if we can rename RegToRename in this instruction ----
1407 // * collect the registers used and required register classes for RegToRename. ----
1408 std::function CheckMIs = [&](MachineInstr &MI, 0
1409 bool IsDef) { ----
1410 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Checking " << MI << "\n"); 0
1411 // Currently we do not try to rename across frame-setup instructions. ----
1412 if (MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup)) { 0
1413 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Cannot rename framesetup instructions currently (" 0
1414 << MI << ")\n"); ----
1415 return false; 0
1416 } ----
1417 ----
1418 UsedInBetween.accumulate(MI); 0
1419 ----
1420 // For a definition, check that we can rename the definition and exit the ----
1421 // loop. ----
1422 FoundDef = IsDef; 0
1423 ----
1424 // For defs, check if we can rename the first def of RegToRename. ----
1425 if (FoundDef) { 0
1426 // For some pseudo instructions, we might not generate code in the end ----
1427 // (e.g. KILL) and we would end up without a correct def for the rename ----
1428 // register. ----
1429 // TODO: This might be overly conservative and we could handle those cases ----
1430 // in multiple ways: ----
1431 // 1. Insert an extra copy, to materialize the def. ----
1432 // 2. Skip pseudo-defs until we find an non-pseudo def. ----
1433 if (MI.isPseudo()) { 0
1434 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Cannot rename pseudo instruction " << MI 0
1435 << "\n"); ----
1436 return false; 0
1437 } ----
1438 ----
1439 for (auto &MOP : MI.operands()) { 0
1440 if (!MOP.isReg() || !MOP.isDef() || MOP.isDebug() || !MOP.getReg() || 0
1441 !TRI->regsOverlap(MOP.getReg(), RegToRename)) 0
1442 continue; 0
1443 if (!canRenameMOP(MOP)) { 0
1444 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() 0
1445 << " Cannot rename " << MOP << " in " << MI << "\n"); ----
1446 return false; 0
1447 } ----
1448 RequiredClasses.insert(TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(MOP.getReg())); 0
1449 } ----
1450 return true; 0
1451 } else { ----
1452 for (auto &MOP : MI.operands()) { 0
1453 if (!MOP.isReg() || MOP.isDebug() || !MOP.getReg() || 0
1454 !TRI->regsOverlap(MOP.getReg(), RegToRename)) 0
1455 continue; 0
1456 ----
1457 if (!canRenameMOP(MOP)) { 0
1458 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() 0
1459 << " Cannot rename " << MOP << " in " << MI << "\n"); ----
1460 return false; 0
1461 } ----
1462 RequiredClasses.insert(TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(MOP.getReg())); 0
1463 } ----
1464 } ----
1465 return true; 0
1466 }; 0
1467 ----
1468 if (!forAllMIsUntilDef(FirstMI, RegToRename, TRI, LdStLimit, CheckMIs)) 0
1469 return false; 0
1470 ----
1471 if (!FoundDef) { 0
1472 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Did not find definition for register in BB\n"); 0
1473 return false; 0
1474 } ----
1475 return true; 0
1476 } 0
1477 ----
1478 // Check if we can find a physical register for renaming \p Reg. This register ----
1479 // must: ----
1480 // * not be defined already in \p DefinedInBB; DefinedInBB must contain all ----
1481 // defined registers up to the point where the renamed register will be used, ----
1482 // * not used in \p UsedInBetween; UsedInBetween must contain all accessed ----
1483 // registers in the range the rename register will be used, ----
1484 // * is available in all used register classes (checked using RequiredClasses). ----
1485 static std::optional tryToFindRegisterToRename( 0
1486 const MachineFunction &MF, Register Reg, LiveRegUnits &DefinedInBB, ----
1487 LiveRegUnits &UsedInBetween, ----
1488 SmallPtrSetImpl &RequiredClasses, ----
1489 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
1490 const MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1491 ----
1492 // Checks if any sub- or super-register of PR is callee saved. ----
1493 auto AnySubOrSuperRegCalleePreserved = [&MF, TRI](MCPhysReg PR) { 0
1494 return any_of(TRI->sub_and_superregs_inclusive(PR), 0
1495 [&MF, TRI](MCPhysReg SubOrSuper) { 0
1496 return TRI->isCalleeSavedPhysReg(SubOrSuper, MF); 0
1497 }); 0
1498 }; 0
1499 ----
1500 // Check if PR or one of its sub- or super-registers can be used for all ----
1501 // required register classes. ----
1502 auto CanBeUsedForAllClasses = [&RequiredClasses, TRI](MCPhysReg PR) { 0
1503 return all_of(RequiredClasses, [PR, TRI](const TargetRegisterClass *C) { 0
1504 return any_of(TRI->sub_and_superregs_inclusive(PR), 0
1505 [C, TRI](MCPhysReg SubOrSuper) { 0
1506 return C == TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(SubOrSuper); 0
1507 }); 0
1508 }); 0
1509 }; 0
1510 ----
1511 auto *RegClass = TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(Reg); 0
1512 for (const MCPhysReg &PR : *RegClass) { 0
1513 if (DefinedInBB.available(PR) && UsedInBetween.available(PR) && 0
1514 !RegInfo.isReserved(PR) && !AnySubOrSuperRegCalleePreserved(PR) && 0
1515 CanBeUsedForAllClasses(PR)) { 0
1516 DefinedInBB.addReg(PR); 0
1517 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Found rename register " << printReg(PR, TRI) 0
1518 << "\n"); ----
1519 return {PR}; 0
1520 } ----
1521 } ----
1522 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "No rename register found from " 0
1523 << TRI->getRegClassName(RegClass) << "\n"); ----
1524 return std::nullopt; 0
1525 } ----
1526 ----
1527 /// Scan the instructions looking for a load/store that can be combined with the ----
1528 /// current instruction into a wider equivalent or a load/store pair. ----
1529 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1530 AArch64LoadStoreOpt::findMatchingInsn(MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, 0
1531 LdStPairFlags &Flags, unsigned Limit, ----
1532 bool FindNarrowMerge) { ----
1533 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = I->getParent()->end(); 0
1534 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = I; 0
1535 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBIWithRenameReg; 0
1536 MachineInstr &FirstMI = *I; 0
1537 MBBI = next_nodbg(MBBI, E); 0
1538 ----
1539 bool MayLoad = FirstMI.mayLoad(); 0
1540 bool IsUnscaled = TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(FirstMI); 0
1541 Register Reg = getLdStRegOp(FirstMI).getReg(); 0
1542 Register BaseReg = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(FirstMI).getReg(); 0
1543 int Offset = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(FirstMI).getImm(); 0
1544 int OffsetStride = IsUnscaled ? TII->getMemScale(FirstMI) : 1; 0
1545 bool IsPromotableZeroStore = isPromotableZeroStoreInst(FirstMI); 0
1546 ----
1547 std::optional MaybeCanRename; 0
1548 if (!EnableRenaming) 0
1549 MaybeCanRename = {false}; 0
1550 ----
1551 SmallPtrSet RequiredClasses; 0
1552 LiveRegUnits UsedInBetween; 0
1553 UsedInBetween.init(*TRI); 0
1554 ----
1555 Flags.clearRenameReg(); 0
1556 ----
1557 // Track which register units have been modified and used between the first ----
1558 // insn (inclusive) and the second insn. ----
1559 ModifiedRegUnits.clear(); 0
1560 UsedRegUnits.clear(); 0
1561 ----
1562 // Remember any instructions that read/write memory between FirstMI and MI. ----
1563 SmallVector MemInsns; 0
1564 ----
1565 for (unsigned Count = 0; MBBI != E && Count < Limit; 0
1566 MBBI = next_nodbg(MBBI, E)) { 0
1567 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1568 ----
1569 UsedInBetween.accumulate(MI); 0
1570 ----
1571 // Don't count transient instructions towards the search limit since there ----
1572 // may be different numbers of them if e.g. debug information is present. ----
1573 if (!MI.isTransient()) 0
1574 ++Count; 0
1575 ----
1576 Flags.setSExtIdx(-1); 0
1577 if (areCandidatesToMergeOrPair(FirstMI, MI, Flags, TII) && 0
1578 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MI).isImm()) { 0
1579 assert(MI.mayLoadOrStore() && "Expected memory operation."); 0
1580 // If we've found another instruction with the same opcode, check to see ----
1581 // if the base and offset are compatible with our starting instruction. ----
1582 // These instructions all have scaled immediate operands, so we just ----
1583 // check for +1/-1. Make sure to check the new instruction offset is ----
1584 // actually an immediate and not a symbolic reference destined for ----
1585 // a relocation. ----
1586 Register MIBaseReg = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MI).getReg(); 0
1587 int MIOffset = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MI).getImm(); 0
1588 bool MIIsUnscaled = TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(MI); 0
1589 if (IsUnscaled != MIIsUnscaled) { 0
1590 // We're trying to pair instructions that differ in how they are scaled. ----
1591 // If FirstMI is scaled then scale the offset of MI accordingly. ----
1592 // Otherwise, do the opposite (i.e., make MI's offset unscaled). ----
1593 int MemSize = TII->getMemScale(MI); 0
1594 if (MIIsUnscaled) { 0
1595 // If the unscaled offset isn't a multiple of the MemSize, we can't ----
1596 // pair the operations together: bail and keep looking. ----
1597 if (MIOffset % MemSize) { 0
1598 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, 0
1599 UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1600 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1601 continue; 0
1602 } ----
1603 MIOffset /= MemSize; 0
1604 } else { ----
1605 MIOffset *= MemSize; 0
1606 } ----
1607 } ----
1608 ----
1609 bool IsPreLdSt = isPreLdStPairCandidate(FirstMI, MI); 0
1610 ----
1611 if (BaseReg == MIBaseReg) { 0
1612 // If the offset of the second ld/st is not equal to the size of the ----
1613 // destination register it can’t be paired with a pre-index ld/st ----
1614 // pair. Additionally if the base reg is used or modified the operations ----
1615 // can't be paired: bail and keep looking. ----
1616 if (IsPreLdSt) { 0
1617 bool IsOutOfBounds = MIOffset != TII->getMemScale(MI); 0
1618 bool IsBaseRegUsed = !UsedRegUnits.available( 0
1619 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MI).getReg()); 0
1620 bool IsBaseRegModified = !ModifiedRegUnits.available( 0
1621 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MI).getReg()); 0
1622 // If the stored value and the address of the second instruction is ----
1623 // the same, it needs to be using the updated register and therefore ----
1624 // it must not be folded. ----
1625 bool IsMIRegTheSame = ----
1626 TRI->regsOverlap(getLdStRegOp(MI).getReg(), 0
1627 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MI).getReg()); 0
1628 if (IsOutOfBounds || IsBaseRegUsed || IsBaseRegModified || 0
1629 IsMIRegTheSame) { ----
1630 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, 0
1631 UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1632 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1633 continue; 0
1634 } ----
1635 } else { ----
1636 if ((Offset != MIOffset + OffsetStride) && 0
1637 (Offset + OffsetStride != MIOffset)) { 0
1638 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, 0
1639 UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1640 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1641 continue; 0
1642 } ----
1643 } ----
1644 ----
1645 int MinOffset = Offset < MIOffset ? Offset : MIOffset; 0
1646 if (FindNarrowMerge) { 0
1647 // If the alignment requirements of the scaled wide load/store ----
1648 // instruction can't express the offset of the scaled narrow input, ----
1649 // bail and keep looking. For promotable zero stores, allow only when ----
1650 // the stored value is the same (i.e., WZR). ----
1651 if ((!IsUnscaled && alignTo(MinOffset, 2) != MinOffset) || 0
1652 (IsPromotableZeroStore && Reg != getLdStRegOp(MI).getReg())) { 0
1653 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, 0
1654 UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1655 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1656 continue; 0
1657 } ----
1658 } else { ----
1659 // Pairwise instructions have a 7-bit signed offset field. Single ----
1660 // insns have a 12-bit unsigned offset field. If the resultant ----
1661 // immediate offset of merging these instructions is out of range for ----
1662 // a pairwise instruction, bail and keep looking. ----
1663 if (!inBoundsForPair(IsUnscaled, MinOffset, OffsetStride)) { 0
1664 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, 0
1665 UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1666 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1667 continue; 0
1668 } ----
1669 // If the alignment requirements of the paired (scaled) instruction ----
1670 // can't express the offset of the unscaled input, bail and keep ----
1671 // looking. ----
1672 if (IsUnscaled && (alignTo(MinOffset, OffsetStride) != MinOffset)) { 0
1673 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, 0
1674 UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1675 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1676 continue; 0
1677 } ----
1678 } ----
1679 // If the destination register of one load is the same register or a ----
1680 // sub/super register of the other load, bail and keep looking. A ----
1681 // load-pair instruction with both destination registers the same is ----
1682 // UNPREDICTABLE and will result in an exception. ----
1683 if (MayLoad && 0
1684 TRI->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(Reg, getLdStRegOp(MI).getReg())) { 0
1685 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, UsedRegUnits, 0
1686 TRI); ----
1687 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1688 continue; 0
1689 } ----
1690 ----
1691 // If the BaseReg has been modified, then we cannot do the optimization. ----
1692 // For example, in the following pattern ----
1693 // ldr x1 [x2] ----
1694 // ldr x2 [x3] ----
1695 // ldr x4 [x2, #8], ----
1696 // the first and third ldr cannot be converted to ldp x1, x4, [x2] ----
1697 if (!ModifiedRegUnits.available(BaseReg)) 0
1698 return E; 0
1699 ----
1700 // If the Rt of the second instruction was not modified or used between ----
1701 // the two instructions and none of the instructions between the second ----
1702 // and first alias with the second, we can combine the second into the ----
1703 // first. ----
1704 if (ModifiedRegUnits.available(getLdStRegOp(MI).getReg()) && 0
1705 !(MI.mayLoad() && 0
1706 !UsedRegUnits.available(getLdStRegOp(MI).getReg())) && 0
1707 !mayAlias(MI, MemInsns, AA)) { 0
1708 ----
1709 Flags.setMergeForward(false); 0
1710 Flags.clearRenameReg(); 0
1711 return MBBI; 0
1712 } ----
1713 ----
1714 // Likewise, if the Rt of the first instruction is not modified or used ----
1715 // between the two instructions and none of the instructions between the ----
1716 // first and the second alias with the first, we can combine the first ----
1717 // into the second. ----
1718 if (!(MayLoad && 0
1719 !UsedRegUnits.available(getLdStRegOp(FirstMI).getReg())) && 0
1720 !mayAlias(FirstMI, MemInsns, AA)) { 0
1721 ----
1722 if (ModifiedRegUnits.available(getLdStRegOp(FirstMI).getReg())) { 0
1723 Flags.setMergeForward(true); 0
1724 Flags.clearRenameReg(); 0
1725 return MBBI; 0
1726 } ----
1727 ----
1728 if (DebugCounter::shouldExecute(RegRenamingCounter)) { 0
1729 if (!MaybeCanRename) 0
1730 MaybeCanRename = {canRenameUpToDef(FirstMI, UsedInBetween, 0
1731 RequiredClasses, TRI)}; ----
1732 ----
1733 if (*MaybeCanRename) { 0
1734 std::optional MaybeRenameReg = ----
1735 tryToFindRegisterToRename(*FirstMI.getParent()->getParent(), 0
1736 Reg, DefinedInBB, UsedInBetween, 0
1737 RequiredClasses, TRI); ----
1738 if (MaybeRenameReg) { 0
1739 Flags.setRenameReg(*MaybeRenameReg); 0
1740 Flags.setMergeForward(true); 0
1741 MBBIWithRenameReg = MBBI; 0
1742 } ----
1743 } ----
1744 } ----
1745 } ----
1746 // Unable to combine these instructions due to interference in between. ----
1747 // Keep looking. ----
1748 } ----
1749 } ----
1750 ----
1751 if (Flags.getRenameReg()) 0
1752 return MBBIWithRenameReg; 0
1753 ----
1754 // If the instruction wasn't a matching load or store. Stop searching if we ----
1755 // encounter a call instruction that might modify memory. ----
1756 if (MI.isCall()) 0
1757 return E; 0
1758 ----
1759 // Update modified / uses register units. ----
1760 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1761 ----
1762 // Otherwise, if the base register is modified, we have no match, so ----
1763 // return early. ----
1764 if (!ModifiedRegUnits.available(BaseReg)) 0
1765 return E; 0
1766 ----
1767 // Update list of instructions that read/write memory. ----
1768 if (MI.mayLoadOrStore()) 0
1769 MemInsns.push_back(&MI); 0
1770 } ----
1771 return E; 0
1772 } 0
1773 ----
1774 static MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1775 maybeMoveCFI(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock::iterator MaybeCFI) { 0
1776 auto End = MI.getParent()->end(); 0
1777 if (MaybeCFI == End || 0
1778 MaybeCFI->getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::CFI_INSTRUCTION || 0
1779 !(MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup) || 0
1780 MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameDestroy)) || 0
1781 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MI).getReg() != AArch64::SP) 0
1782 return End; 0
1783 ----
1784 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent(); 0
1785 unsigned CFIIndex = MaybeCFI->getOperand(0).getCFIIndex(); 0
1786 const MCCFIInstruction &CFI = MF.getFrameInstructions()[CFIIndex]; 0
1787 switch (CFI.getOperation()) { 0
1788 case MCCFIInstruction::OpDefCfa: 0
1789 case MCCFIInstruction::OpDefCfaOffset: ----
1790 return MaybeCFI; 0
1791 default: 0
1792 return End; 0
1793 } ----
1794 } ----
1795 ----
1796 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1797 AArch64LoadStoreOpt::mergeUpdateInsn(MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, 0
1798 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Update, ----
1799 bool IsPreIdx) { ----
1800 assert((Update->getOpcode() == AArch64::ADDXri || 0
1801 Update->getOpcode() == AArch64::SUBXri) && ----
1802 "Unexpected base register update instruction to merge!"); ----
1803 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = I->getParent()->end(); 0
1804 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NextI = next_nodbg(I, E); 0
1805 ----
1806 // If updating the SP and the following instruction is CFA offset related CFI ----
1807 // instruction move it after the merged instruction. ----
1808 MachineBasicBlock::iterator CFI = ----
1809 IsPreIdx ? maybeMoveCFI(*Update, next_nodbg(Update, E)) : E; 0
1810 ----
1811 // Return the instruction following the merged instruction, which is ----
1812 // the instruction following our unmerged load. Unless that's the add/sub ----
1813 // instruction we're merging, in which case it's the one after that. ----
1814 if (NextI == Update) 0
1815 NextI = next_nodbg(NextI, E); 0
1816 ----
1817 int Value = Update->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1818 assert(AArch64_AM::getShiftValue(Update->getOperand(3).getImm()) == 0 && 0
1819 "Can't merge 1 << 12 offset into pre-/post-indexed load / store"); ----
1820 if (Update->getOpcode() == AArch64::SUBXri) 0
1821 Value = -Value; 0
1822 ----
1823 unsigned NewOpc = IsPreIdx ? getPreIndexedOpcode(I->getOpcode()) 0
1824 : getPostIndexedOpcode(I->getOpcode()); 0
1825 MachineInstrBuilder MIB; 0
1826 int Scale, MinOffset, MaxOffset; ----
1827 getPrePostIndexedMemOpInfo(*I, Scale, MinOffset, MaxOffset); 0
1828 if (!AArch64InstrInfo::isPairedLdSt(*I)) { 0
1829 // Non-paired instruction. ----
1830 MIB = BuildMI(*I->getParent(), I, I->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1831 .add(getLdStRegOp(*Update)) 0
1832 .add(getLdStRegOp(*I)) 0
1833 .add(AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(*I)) 0
1834 .addImm(Value / Scale) 0
1835 .setMemRefs(I->memoperands()) 0
1836 .setMIFlags(I->mergeFlagsWith(*Update)); 0
1837 } else { ----
1838 // Paired instruction. ----
1839 MIB = BuildMI(*I->getParent(), I, I->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1840 .add(getLdStRegOp(*Update)) 0
1841 .add(getLdStRegOp(*I, 0)) 0
1842 .add(getLdStRegOp(*I, 1)) 0
1843 .add(AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(*I)) 0
1844 .addImm(Value / Scale) 0
1845 .setMemRefs(I->memoperands()) 0
1846 .setMIFlags(I->mergeFlagsWith(*Update)); 0
1847 } ----
1848 if (CFI != E) { 0
1849 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = I->getParent(); 0
1850 MBB->splice(std::next(MIB.getInstr()->getIterator()), MBB, CFI); 0
1851 } ----
1852 ----
1853 if (IsPreIdx) { 0
1854 ++NumPreFolded; 0
1855 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Creating pre-indexed load/store."); 0
1856 } else { ----
1857 ++NumPostFolded; 0
1858 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Creating post-indexed load/store."); 0
1859 } ----
1860 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Replacing instructions:\n "); 0
1861 LLVM_DEBUG(I->print(dbgs())); 0
1862 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "); 0
1863 LLVM_DEBUG(Update->print(dbgs())); 0
1864 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " with instruction:\n "); 0
1865 LLVM_DEBUG(((MachineInstr *)MIB)->print(dbgs())); 0
1866 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1867 ----
1868 // Erase the old instructions for the block. ----
1869 I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1870 Update->eraseFromParent(); 0
1871 ----
1872 return NextI; 0
1873 } ----
1874 ----
1875 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::isMatchingUpdateInsn(MachineInstr &MemMI, 0
1876 MachineInstr &MI, ----
1877 unsigned BaseReg, int Offset) { ----
1878 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1879 default: 0
1880 break; 0
1881 case AArch64::SUBXri: 0
1882 case AArch64::ADDXri: ----
1883 // Make sure it's a vanilla immediate operand, not a relocation or ----
1884 // anything else we can't handle. ----
1885 if (!MI.getOperand(2).isImm()) 0
1886 break; 0
1887 // Watch out for 1 << 12 shifted value. ----
1888 if (AArch64_AM::getShiftValue(MI.getOperand(3).getImm())) 0
1889 break; 0
1890 ----
1891 // The update instruction source and destination register must be the ----
1892 // same as the load/store base register. ----
1893 if (MI.getOperand(0).getReg() != BaseReg || 0
1894 MI.getOperand(1).getReg() != BaseReg) 0
1895 break; 0
1896 ----
1897 int UpdateOffset = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1898 if (MI.getOpcode() == AArch64::SUBXri) 0
1899 UpdateOffset = -UpdateOffset; 0
1900 ----
1901 // The immediate must be a multiple of the scaling factor of the pre/post ----
1902 // indexed instruction. ----
1903 int Scale, MinOffset, MaxOffset; ----
1904 getPrePostIndexedMemOpInfo(MemMI, Scale, MinOffset, MaxOffset); 0
1905 if (UpdateOffset % Scale != 0) 0
1906 break; 0
1907 ----
1908 // Scaled offset must fit in the instruction immediate. ----
1909 int ScaledOffset = UpdateOffset / Scale; 0
1910 if (ScaledOffset > MaxOffset || ScaledOffset < MinOffset) 0
1911 break; ----
1912 ----
1913 // If we have a non-zero Offset, we check that it matches the amount ----
1914 // we're adding to the register. ----
1915 if (!Offset || Offset == UpdateOffset) 0
1916 return true; 0
1917 break; 0
1918 } ----
1919 return false; 0
1920 } ----
1921 ----
1922 MachineBasicBlock::iterator AArch64LoadStoreOpt::findMatchingUpdateInsnForward( 0
1923 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, int UnscaledOffset, unsigned Limit) { ----
1924 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = I->getParent()->end(); 0
1925 MachineInstr &MemMI = *I; 0
1926 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = I; 0
1927 ----
1928 Register BaseReg = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MemMI).getReg(); 0
1929 int MIUnscaledOffset = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MemMI).getImm() * 0
1930 TII->getMemScale(MemMI); 0
1931 ----
1932 // Scan forward looking for post-index opportunities. Updating instructions ----
1933 // can't be formed if the memory instruction doesn't have the offset we're ----
1934 // looking for. ----
1935 if (MIUnscaledOffset != UnscaledOffset) 0
1936 return E; 0
1937 ----
1938 // If the base register overlaps a source/destination register, we can't ----
1939 // merge the update. This does not apply to tag store instructions which ----
1940 // ignore the address part of the source register. ----
1941 // This does not apply to STGPi as well, which does not have unpredictable ----
1942 // behavior in this case unlike normal stores, and always performs writeback ----
1943 // after reading the source register value. ----
1944 if (!isTagStore(MemMI) && MemMI.getOpcode() != AArch64::STGPi) { 0
1945 bool IsPairedInsn = AArch64InstrInfo::isPairedLdSt(MemMI); 0
1946 for (unsigned i = 0, e = IsPairedInsn ? 2 : 1; i != e; ++i) { 0
1947 Register DestReg = getLdStRegOp(MemMI, i).getReg(); 0
1948 if (DestReg == BaseReg || TRI->isSubRegister(BaseReg, DestReg)) 0
1949 return E; 0
1950 } ----
1951 } ----
1952 ----
1953 // Track which register units have been modified and used between the first ----
1954 // insn (inclusive) and the second insn. ----
1955 ModifiedRegUnits.clear(); 0
1956 UsedRegUnits.clear(); 0
1957 MBBI = next_nodbg(MBBI, E); 0
1958 ----
1959 // We can't post-increment the stack pointer if any instruction between ----
1960 // the memory access (I) and the increment (MBBI) can access the memory ----
1961 // region defined by [SP, MBBI]. ----
1962 const bool BaseRegSP = BaseReg == AArch64::SP; 0
1963 if (BaseRegSP && needsWinCFI(I->getMF())) { 0
1964 // FIXME: For now, we always block the optimization over SP in windows ----
1965 // targets as it requires to adjust the unwind/debug info, messing up ----
1966 // the unwind info can actually cause a miscompile. ----
1967 return E; 0
1968 } ----
1969 ----
1970 for (unsigned Count = 0; MBBI != E && Count < Limit; 0
1971 MBBI = next_nodbg(MBBI, E)) { 0
1972 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
1973 ----
1974 // Don't count transient instructions towards the search limit since there ----
1975 // may be different numbers of them if e.g. debug information is present. ----
1976 if (!MI.isTransient()) 0
1977 ++Count; 0
1978 ----
1979 // If we found a match, return it. ----
1980 if (isMatchingUpdateInsn(*I, MI, BaseReg, UnscaledOffset)) 0
1981 return MBBI; 0
1982 ----
1983 // Update the status of what the instruction clobbered and used. ----
1984 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
1985 ----
1986 // Otherwise, if the base register is used or modified, we have no match, so ----
1987 // return early. ----
1988 // If we are optimizing SP, do not allow instructions that may load or store ----
1989 // in between the load and the optimized value update. ----
1990 if (!ModifiedRegUnits.available(BaseReg) || 0
1991 !UsedRegUnits.available(BaseReg) || 0
1992 (BaseRegSP && MBBI->mayLoadOrStore())) 0
1993 return E; 0
1994 } ----
1995 return E; 0
1996 } ----
1997 ----
1998 MachineBasicBlock::iterator AArch64LoadStoreOpt::findMatchingUpdateInsnBackward( 0
1999 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, unsigned Limit) { ----
2000 MachineBasicBlock::iterator B = I->getParent()->begin(); 0
2001 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = I->getParent()->end(); 0
2002 MachineInstr &MemMI = *I; 0
2003 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = I; 0
2004 MachineFunction &MF = *MemMI.getMF(); 0
2005 ----
2006 Register BaseReg = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStBaseOp(MemMI).getReg(); 0
2007 int Offset = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MemMI).getImm(); 0
2008 ----
2009 // If the load/store is the first instruction in the block, there's obviously ----
2010 // not any matching update. Ditto if the memory offset isn't zero. ----
2011 if (MBBI == B || Offset != 0) 0
2012 return E; 0
2013 // If the base register overlaps a destination register, we can't ----
2014 // merge the update. ----
2015 if (!isTagStore(MemMI)) { 0
2016 bool IsPairedInsn = AArch64InstrInfo::isPairedLdSt(MemMI); 0
2017 for (unsigned i = 0, e = IsPairedInsn ? 2 : 1; i != e; ++i) { 0
2018 Register DestReg = getLdStRegOp(MemMI, i).getReg(); 0
2019 if (DestReg == BaseReg || TRI->isSubRegister(BaseReg, DestReg)) 0
2020 return E; 0
2021 } ----
2022 } ----
2023 ----
2024 const bool BaseRegSP = BaseReg == AArch64::SP; 0
2025 if (BaseRegSP && needsWinCFI(I->getMF())) { 0
2026 // FIXME: For now, we always block the optimization over SP in windows ----
2027 // targets as it requires to adjust the unwind/debug info, messing up ----
2028 // the unwind info can actually cause a miscompile. ----
2029 return E; 0
2030 } ----
2031 ----
2032 const AArch64Subtarget &Subtarget = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
2033 unsigned RedZoneSize = ----
2034 Subtarget.getTargetLowering()->getRedZoneSize(MF.getFunction()); 0
2035 ----
2036 // Track which register units have been modified and used between the first ----
2037 // insn (inclusive) and the second insn. ----
2038 ModifiedRegUnits.clear(); 0
2039 UsedRegUnits.clear(); 0
2040 unsigned Count = 0; 0
2041 bool MemAcessBeforeSPPreInc = false; 0
2042 do { ----
2043 MBBI = prev_nodbg(MBBI, B); 0
2044 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2045 ----
2046 // Don't count transient instructions towards the search limit since there ----
2047 // may be different numbers of them if e.g. debug information is present. ----
2048 if (!MI.isTransient()) 0
2049 ++Count; 0
2050 ----
2051 // If we found a match, return it. ----
2052 if (isMatchingUpdateInsn(*I, MI, BaseReg, Offset)) { 0
2053 // Check that the update value is within our red zone limit (which may be ----
2054 // zero). ----
2055 if (MemAcessBeforeSPPreInc && MBBI->getOperand(2).getImm() > RedZoneSize) 0
2056 return E; 0
2057 return MBBI; 0
2058 } ----
2059 ----
2060 // Update the status of what the instruction clobbered and used. ----
2061 LiveRegUnits::accumulateUsedDefed(MI, ModifiedRegUnits, UsedRegUnits, TRI); 0
2062 ----
2063 // Otherwise, if the base register is used or modified, we have no match, so ----
2064 // return early. ----
2065 if (!ModifiedRegUnits.available(BaseReg) || 0
2066 !UsedRegUnits.available(BaseReg)) 0
2067 return E; 0
2068 // Keep track if we have a memory access before an SP pre-increment, in this ----
2069 // case we need to validate later that the update amount respects the red ----
2070 // zone. ----
2071 if (BaseRegSP && MBBI->mayLoadOrStore()) 0
2072 MemAcessBeforeSPPreInc = true; 0
2073 } while (MBBI != B && Count < Limit); 0
2074 return E; 0
2075 } ----
2076 ----
2077 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::tryToPromoteLoadFromStore( 0
2078 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { ----
2079 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2080 // If this is a volatile load, don't mess with it. ----
2081 if (MI.hasOrderedMemoryRef()) 0
2082 return false; 0
2083 ----
2084 if (needsWinCFI(MI.getMF()) && MI.getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameDestroy)) 0
2085 return false; 0
2086 ----
2087 // Make sure this is a reg+imm. ----
2088 // FIXME: It is possible to extend it to handle reg+reg cases. ----
2089 if (!AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MI).isImm()) 0
2090 return false; 0
2091 ----
2092 // Look backward up to LdStLimit instructions. ----
2093 MachineBasicBlock::iterator StoreI; 0
2094 if (findMatchingStore(MBBI, LdStLimit, StoreI)) { 0
2095 ++NumLoadsFromStoresPromoted; 0
2096 // Promote the load. Keeping the iterator straight is a ----
2097 // pain, so we let the merge routine tell us what the next instruction ----
2098 // is after it's done mucking about. ----
2099 MBBI = promoteLoadFromStore(MBBI, StoreI); 0
2100 return true; 0
2101 } ----
2102 return false; 0
2103 } ----
2104 ----
2105 // Merge adjacent zero stores into a wider store. ----
2106 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::tryToMergeZeroStInst( 0
2107 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { ----
2108 assert(isPromotableZeroStoreInst(*MBBI) && "Expected narrow store."); 0
2109 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2110 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = MI.getParent()->end(); 0
2111 ----
2112 if (!TII->isCandidateToMergeOrPair(MI)) 0
2113 return false; 0
2114 ----
2115 // Look ahead up to LdStLimit instructions for a mergable instruction. ----
2116 LdStPairFlags Flags; 0
2117 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MergeMI = ----
2118 findMatchingInsn(MBBI, Flags, LdStLimit, /* FindNarrowMerge = */ true); 0
2119 if (MergeMI != E) { 0
2120 ++NumZeroStoresPromoted; 0
2121 ----
2122 // Keeping the iterator straight is a pain, so we let the merge routine tell ----
2123 // us what the next instruction is after it's done mucking about. ----
2124 MBBI = mergeNarrowZeroStores(MBBI, MergeMI, Flags); 0
2125 return true; 0
2126 } ----
2127 return false; 0
2128 } ----
2129 ----
2130 // Find loads and stores that can be merged into a single load or store pair ----
2131 // instruction. ----
2132 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::tryToPairLdStInst(MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { 0
2133 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2134 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = MI.getParent()->end(); 0
2135 ----
2136 if (!TII->isCandidateToMergeOrPair(MI)) 0
2137 return false; 0
2138 ----
2139 // Early exit if the offset is not possible to match. (6 bits of positive ----
2140 // range, plus allow an extra one in case we find a later insn that matches ----
2141 // with Offset-1) ----
2142 bool IsUnscaled = TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(MI); 0
2143 int Offset = AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MI).getImm(); 0
2144 int OffsetStride = IsUnscaled ? TII->getMemScale(MI) : 1; 0
2145 // Allow one more for offset. ----
2146 if (Offset > 0) 0
2147 Offset -= OffsetStride; 0
2148 if (!inBoundsForPair(IsUnscaled, Offset, OffsetStride)) 0
2149 return false; 0
2150 ----
2151 // Look ahead up to LdStLimit instructions for a pairable instruction. ----
2152 LdStPairFlags Flags; 0
2153 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Paired = ----
2154 findMatchingInsn(MBBI, Flags, LdStLimit, /* FindNarrowMerge = */ false); 0
2155 if (Paired != E) { 0
2156 ++NumPairCreated; 0
2157 if (TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(MI)) 0
2158 ++NumUnscaledPairCreated; 0
2159 // Keeping the iterator straight is a pain, so we let the merge routine tell ----
2160 // us what the next instruction is after it's done mucking about. ----
2161 auto Prev = std::prev(MBBI); 0
2162 MBBI = mergePairedInsns(MBBI, Paired, Flags); 0
2163 // Collect liveness info for instructions between Prev and the new position ----
2164 // MBBI. ----
2165 for (auto I = std::next(Prev); I != MBBI; I++) 0
2166 updateDefinedRegisters(*I, DefinedInBB, TRI); 0
2167 ----
2168 return true; 0
2169 } ----
2170 return false; 0
2171 } ----
2172 ----
2173 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::tryToMergeLdStUpdate 0
2174 (MachineBasicBlock::iterator &MBBI) { ----
2175 MachineInstr &MI = *MBBI; 0
2176 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = MI.getParent()->end(); 0
2177 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Update; 0
2178 ----
2179 // Look forward to try to form a post-index instruction. For example, ----
2180 // ldr x0, [x20] ----
2181 // add x20, x20, #32 ----
2182 // merged into: ----
2183 // ldr x0, [x20], #32 ----
2184 Update = findMatchingUpdateInsnForward(MBBI, 0, UpdateLimit); 0
2185 if (Update != E) { 0
2186 // Merge the update into the ld/st. ----
2187 MBBI = mergeUpdateInsn(MBBI, Update, /*IsPreIdx=*/false); 0
2188 return true; 0
2189 } ----
2190 ----
2191 // Don't know how to handle unscaled pre/post-index versions below, so bail. ----
2192 if (TII->hasUnscaledLdStOffset(MI.getOpcode())) 0
2193 return false; 0
2194 ----
2195 // Look back to try to find a pre-index instruction. For example, ----
2196 // add x0, x0, #8 ----
2197 // ldr x1, [x0] ----
2198 // merged into: ----
2199 // ldr x1, [x0, #8]! ----
2200 Update = findMatchingUpdateInsnBackward(MBBI, UpdateLimit); 0
2201 if (Update != E) { 0
2202 // Merge the update into the ld/st. ----
2203 MBBI = mergeUpdateInsn(MBBI, Update, /*IsPreIdx=*/true); 0
2204 return true; 0
2205 } ----
2206 ----
2207 // The immediate in the load/store is scaled by the size of the memory ----
2208 // operation. The immediate in the add we're looking for, ----
2209 // however, is not, so adjust here. ----
2210 int UnscaledOffset = ----
2211 AArch64InstrInfo::getLdStOffsetOp(MI).getImm() * TII->getMemScale(MI); 0
2212 ----
2213 // Look forward to try to find a pre-index instruction. For example, ----
2214 // ldr x1, [x0, #64] ----
2215 // add x0, x0, #64 ----
2216 // merged into: ----
2217 // ldr x1, [x0, #64]! ----
2218 Update = findMatchingUpdateInsnForward(MBBI, UnscaledOffset, UpdateLimit); 0
2219 if (Update != E) { 0
2220 // Merge the update into the ld/st. ----

2228 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::optimizeBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
2229 bool EnableNarrowZeroStOpt) { ----
2230 ----
2231 bool Modified = false; 0
2232 // Four tranformations to do here: ----
2233 // 1) Find loads that directly read from stores and promote them by ----
2234 // replacing with mov instructions. If the store is wider than the load, ----
2235 // the load will be replaced with a bitfield extract. ----
2236 // e.g., ----
2237 // str w1, [x0, #4] ----
2238 // ldrh w2, [x0, #6] ----
2239 // ; becomes ----
2240 // str w1, [x0, #4] ----
2241 // lsr w2, w1, #16 ----
2242 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); 0
2243 MBBI != E;) { 0
2244 if (isPromotableLoadFromStore(*MBBI) && tryToPromoteLoadFromStore(MBBI)) 0
2245 Modified = true; 0
2246 else ----
2247 ++MBBI; 0
2248 } ----
2249 // 2) Merge adjacent zero stores into a wider store. ----
2250 // e.g., ----
2251 // strh wzr, [x0] ----
2252 // strh wzr, [x0, #2] ----
2253 // ; becomes ----
2254 // str wzr, [x0] ----
2255 // e.g., ----
2256 // str wzr, [x0] ----
2257 // str wzr, [x0, #4] ----
2258 // ; becomes ----
2259 // str xzr, [x0] ----
2260 if (EnableNarrowZeroStOpt) 0
2261 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); 0
2262 MBBI != E;) { 0
2263 if (isPromotableZeroStoreInst(*MBBI) && tryToMergeZeroStInst(MBBI)) 0
2264 Modified = true; 0
2265 else ----
2266 ++MBBI; 0
2267 } ----
2268 // 3) Find loads and stores that can be merged into a single load or store ----
2269 // pair instruction. ----
2270 // e.g., ----
2271 // ldr x0, [x2] ----
2272 // ldr x1, [x2, #8] ----
2273 // ; becomes ----
2274 // ldp x0, x1, [x2] ----
2275 ----
2276 if (MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo().tracksLiveness()) { 0
2277 DefinedInBB.clear(); 0
2278 DefinedInBB.addLiveIns(MBB); 0
2279 } ----
2280 ----
2281 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); 0
2282 MBBI != E;) { 0
2283 // Track currently live registers up to this point, to help with ----
2284 // searching for a rename register on demand. ----
2285 updateDefinedRegisters(*MBBI, DefinedInBB, TRI); 0
2286 if (TII->isPairableLdStInst(*MBBI) && tryToPairLdStInst(MBBI)) 0
2287 Modified = true; 0
2288 else ----
2289 ++MBBI; 0
2290 } ----
2291 // 4) Find base register updates that can be merged into the load or store ----
2292 // as a base-reg writeback. ----
2293 // e.g., ----
2294 // ldr x0, [x2] ----
2295 // add x2, x2, #4 ----
2296 // ; becomes ----
2297 // ldr x0, [x2], #4 ----
2298 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); 0
2299 MBBI != E;) { 0
2300 if (isMergeableLdStUpdate(*MBBI) && tryToMergeLdStUpdate(MBBI)) 0
2301 Modified = true; 0
2302 else ----
2303 ++MBBI; 0
2304 } ----
2305 ----
2306 return Modified; 0
2307 } ----

2309 bool AArch64LoadStoreOpt::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &Fn) { 0
2310 if (skipFunction(Fn.getFunction())) 0
2311 return false; 0
2312 ----
2313 Subtarget = &Fn.getSubtarget(); 0
2314 TII = static_cast(Subtarget->getInstrInfo()); 0
2315 TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo(); 0
2316 AA = &getAnalysis().getAAResults(); 0
2317 ----
2318 // Resize the modified and used register unit trackers. We do this once ----
2319 // per function and then clear the register units each time we optimize a load ----
2320 // or store. ----
2321 ModifiedRegUnits.init(*TRI); 0
2322 UsedRegUnits.init(*TRI); 0
2323 DefinedInBB.init(*TRI); 0
2324 ----
2325 bool Modified = false; 0
2326 bool enableNarrowZeroStOpt = !Subtarget->requiresStrictAlign(); 0
2327 for (auto &MBB : Fn) { 0
2328 auto M = optimizeBlock(MBB, enableNarrowZeroStOpt); 0
2329 Modified |= M; 0
2330 } ----
2331 ----
2332 return Modified; 0
2333 } ----
2334 ----
2335 // FIXME: Do we need/want a pre-alloc pass like ARM has to try to keep loads and ----
2336 // stores near one another? Note: The pre-RA instruction scheduler already has ----
2337 // hooks to try and schedule pairable loads/stores together to improve pairing ----
2338 // opportunities. Thus, pre-RA pairing pass may not be worth the effort. ----
2339 ----
2340 // FIXME: When pairing store instructions it's very possible for this pass to ----
2341 // hoist a store with a KILL marker above another use (without a KILL marker). ----
2342 // The resulting IR is invalid, but nothing uses the KILL markers after this ----
2343 // pass, so it's never caused a problem in practice. ----
2344 ----

2346 /// load / store optimization pass. ----
